1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,200
To return to the subject of the eternal birth.

2
00:00:03,150 --> 00:00:08,637
There is the question whether the soul brings forth the eternal Word in images or imageless?

3
00:00:08,637 --> 00:00:10,037
Remember this.

4
00:00:10,037 --> 00:00:18,062
When the soul resigns herself to God and is atoned with him and God undertakes her work, she is receptive merely and leaves God to act.

5
00:00:18,062 --> 00:00:30,300
Here the soul is pregnant without form or image, for anything conceived in form or image trenches upon time and place and is akin to creatures; whence it follows that the more the work is of the soul the less it is of God.

6
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:37,250
The soul conceives more truly without images than in them, for this birth is more by way of Godhood than of selfhood.

7
00:00:37,250 --> 00:00:43,575
But we may still enquire, in which image does the soul best succeed in giving birth to the eternal Word?

8
00:00:43,575 --> 00:00:45,737
There are three kinds of images.

9
00:00:45,737 --> 00:00:49,462
The first the soul takes in from without through the senses.

10
00:00:49,462 --> 00:00:58,750
The second the soul conjures up from within by thinking on the childhood of our Lord or on his martyrdom; but all images so gotten are called divine births in the soul.

11
00:00:58,750 --> 00:01:02,825
The third kind of images is given to the soul by God direct.

12
00:01:02,825 --> 00:01:06,362
It is in these last that the soul conceives the best.

13
00:01:06,362 --> 00:01:28,600
According to another gloss: this happens when the mind engenders, feels and knows the eternal Word in its proper image as gotten by the Father in himself, supposing the soul able to attain thereto; or, intellect failing her for this, when, faring forth in faith and love, he reaches out to this same image: for in this final image the eternal Word is born most perfectly of all.

14
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:33,737
Another question is, whether the birth of the eternal Word is fleeting or essential?

15
00:01:33,737 --> 00:01:43,450
Now you must understand that it is this birth which unifies the soul, and in this respect it is intrinsic and passes not away unless a man should fall into mortal sin.

16
00:01:43,450 --> 00:01:49,262
But as happening in the sensible perceptions and in the discursive mind this birth is fugitive.

17
00:01:49,262 --> 00:01:55,525
Further, it is asked, in what particular place does the soul bring forth or seek the eternal Word?

18
00:01:55,525 --> 00:01:56,437
Mark.

19
00:01:56,437 --> 00:02:05,637
It is in the Father as the intellectual image of his divine essence and is the reflection of his divine nature, so that it embodies both his essence and his nature.

20
00:02:05,637 --> 00:02:08,600
It is with the Father as the filial Person.

21
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:13,187
It is in the Holy Ghost as the exuberance of their eternal satisfaction.

22
00:02:13,187 --> 00:02:17,875
It is in the soul as the likeness of God’s equal forms (or Persons).

23
00:02:17,875 --> 00:02:21,312
It is in all creatures as the preserver of their being.

24
00:02:21,312 --> 00:02:28,437
It is here the soul must seek the eternal Word, here in these places, and Christ says: ‘Seek and ye shall find.

25
00:02:28,437 --> 00:02:31,200
May we so seek as to find eternally.

26
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:33,462
So help us almighty God.

27
00:02:33,462 --> 00:02:35,987
I will say no more at this collation.

28
00:02:35,987 --> 00:02:38,987
Pray God to fit me for this blessed moment.

29
00:02:38,987 --> 00:02:39,900
Amen.

